KwaZulu-Natal Premier Sihle Zikalala's concerned about the rising number of new Covid-19 infections in the province. #eNCA #DStv403 KWAZULU-NATAL - KwaZulu-Natal Premier Sihle Zikalala is concerned about the rising number of new COVID-19 infections in the province. At over 60,000 - KZN has the most active cases. READ: Over 15,000 new COVID-19 cases reported The province has also breached 5,000 for daily new infections. Zikalala addressed the media on Sunday. READ: COVID-19: Christmas gatherings blamed for Limpopo infections spike The Premier also says more than 700 people have been arrested for flouting COVID-19 regulations in KZN, in the New Year. Watch the video above for more details. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 1 088 889 the total number of deaths is 29 175 and the total number of recoveries is 897 704. pic.twitter.com/mJt1Go519L